&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Medical Workforce Coordinator – AAC &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BAND 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Medical Workforce Coordinator role within the Medical Workforce Department. We are looking for a motivated individual to join our team in providing a comprehensive and high quality Medical HR service to managers and medical staff within the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a varied and demanding agenda and are looking for an enthusiastic individual who wants to develop their career within the NHS. This is a challenging and hands-on operational role, which will see you being one of the first points of contact for Medical Staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be responsible for the planning and management of the consultant medical staff recruitment interview process (AAC’s) following the shortlisting and up until the point the appointment is made. The post holder will liaise with Hospital/ MCS colleagues to confirm dates, panel composition and venue.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will undertake the administration for the Local Clinical Excellence Awards (LCEA), facilitated via the MFT electronic LCEA portal, in line with MFT policy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have a minimum of 12 months experience within Human Resources in a large complex service organisation. Previous NHS experience, working within a Medical Workforce department or knowledge of medical recruitment would be advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have a good standard of education and have experience of carrying an independent workload in an administration role within a busy deadline oriented environment. You should possess an understanding of and a commitment to equal opportunities; be computer literate; highly organised and possess excellent interpersonal and customer focused communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note, only applicants who clearly demonstrate that they meet the essential criteria of the person specification will be considered for interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Chris Tudor, Group Medical Workforce Manager at christine.tudor@mft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameChristine TudorJob titleGroup Medical Workforce ManagerEmail addresschristine.tudor@mft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
